<p><a name="Original_works" id="Original_works"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=C._S._Lewis&amp;action=edit&amp;section=30" title="Edit section: Original works">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Original works</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.wheaton.edu/learnres/wade/" class="external text" title="http://www.wheaton.edu/learnres/wade/" rel="nofollow">Marion E. Wade Center</a> at <a href="/wiki/Wheaton_College,_Illinois" title="Wheaton College, Illinois" class="mw-redirect">Wheaton College</a> — has the world’s largest collection of Lewis's works and works about him</li>
<li><a href="http://www.taylor.edu/academics/supportServices/csLewis/" class="external text" title="http://www.taylor.edu/academics/supportServices/csLewis/" rel="nofollow">Taylor University</a>, Upland, Indiana, has the world's largest private collection of C. S. Lewis first editions, letters, manuscripts, and ephemera — the Edwin W. Brown Collection</li>
</ul>
